Ingredients
4 oz. ginger, scrubbed, thinly sliced (about 1 cup)
1 cup (200 g) sugar
1 lb. fresh strawberries, hulled, quartered, divided
½ cup fresh lime juice (from about 6 limes)
¼ tsp. kosher salt
Club soda and lime wedges (for serving)

Preparation
Step 1
Place four martini glasses in the freezer to chill for at least 30 minutes.

Step 2
Pour 2 cups chilled sparkling water, 2 Tbsp. pomegranate juice, and 2 Tbsp. freshly squeezed lime juice (2 limes) into a large pitcher. Add some ice and stir for 30 seconds to chill the drink. Strain the mixture into the prepared martini glasses, add a few fresh pomegranate seeds and a slice of lime to each glass, and serve ice cold.
